Class TempFileFactory

java.lang.Object
  uk.ac.susx.mlcl.lib.io.TempFileFactory
All Implemented Interfaces:
FileFactory
public class TempFileFactory
extends Object
implements FileFactory

A file FileFactory implementation that creates temporary files using File.createTempFile(java.lang.String, java.lang.String) to produce new files.

Author:
Hamish Morgan <hamish.morgan@sussex.ac.uk>

Constructor Detail

TempFileFactory

public TempFileFactory(String prefix,
                       String suffix,
                       File directory)
                throws NullPointerException,
                       IllegalArgumentException
Construct a new instance of the TempFileFactory, where created files will be stored in the given directory, and will be be named using the provided prefix and suffix. Note that the constraints for suffix and prefix are inherited from File.createTempFile(java.lang.String, java.lang.String); i.e that the prefix must be non-null and at least 3 characters long, but that suffix can be anything. If suffix is null then .tmp is used.

Parameters:
prefix - String that will appended to the start of the name of each created file
suffix - String that will appended to the end of the name of each created file
directory - Create file will be inside this directory
Throws:
NullPointerException - when prefix is null
IllegalArgumentException - when prefix length < 3 characters
